Abnormal anal cytology in HIV-infected women. The purpose of this study was to assess the prevalence of and risk factors for abnormal anal cytology and human papillomavirus (HPV) infections in women who are human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) positive.We conducted an observational single center study of 100 HIV-infected women with cervical and anal specimens that were obtained for cytologic and high-risk HPV testing with Hybrid Capture 2.Seventeen women had abnormal anal cytology 16 women had anal HPVHIV-infected women are at high risk for abnormal cytology and HPV infections of both the anus and cervix. Risk factors for abnormal anal cytology include abnormal cervical cytology, cervical and anal HPV infections, and low CD4 count.